expected could be functionally deleterious and induce a high heterogeneity of
phenotypes at the scale of the whole brain. This raises the interesting
possibility that CNTNAP2 heterozygous missense variants could
define an overall endophenotype shaping a risk for ASD and questions whether,
beyond ASD, the variants could contribute to the development of other
neurodevelopmental disorders and/or genetically less complex pathologies.},
